THE Chinese Embassy in Tanzania has officially started using biometric system in visa application process, according to Ministry of Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation’s press statement released early on Wednesday. The service was launched December, last year. The statement said all visa applicants are “now mandated to visit the embassy physically so that their finger prints would be taken to complete the process. “The system will however exempt applicants who are under 14 and over 70 years of age respectively, those who possess diplomatic and public servant passports.” The new procedure will as well excuse applicant with old passports with less than five years as well as applicants who have problems in their all 10 fingers. The statement also says the embassy intends to improve systems of bilateral interaction between the two countries.